gl_puts() - DERP OS man page

Name -------------------
gl_puts() - puts a string on the scren buffer at the cursor location

Synopsis ---------------

#include "gl_printf.h"

void gl_puts( char *str );

void gl_puts_at(  unsigned int x, unsigned int y, char *str );

Description ------------

The gl_puts function draws a string at the current cursor loccation of 
the user screen buffer. It uses gl.h/draw_character ultimately to draw to 
the screen. The (at) version of this function draws to the provided location
( x, y ).

Return Value -----------

No return value, side effects are a string drawn in the screen buffer.
